      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 250,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Default Edge Type",
        "body": "Base edge type is `reference`. The class upgrades the edge with semantic meaning and defaults, but it does not require a special runtime edge object.",
        "strength": "default",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "rule",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/rule.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/rule.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "rule",
        "markdown": "## Default edge type\n\nUse `reference` unless a host introduces a more specific in-graph content edge type."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "local-content-rule-render",
      "type": "rule",
      "label": "Render Defaults",
      "position": {
        "x": 1840,
        "y": 910
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 250,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Render Defaults",
        "body": "Default render hints: stroke `#7b61ff`, width `2`, dash `solid`, label tone `accent`, routing hint `curved`. Instance overrides may win when present.",
        "strength": "default",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "rule",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/rule.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/rule.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "rule",
        "markdown": "## Render defaults\n\nUse a warm dashed curved path so local content feels exploratory rather than navigational."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "local-content-guardrail",
      "type": "guardrail",
      "label": "Guardrail",
      "position": {
        "x": 880,
        "y": 620
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 250,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "When Not To Use It",
        "body": "Do not use `graph.implements` for dependency, sequence, or weak reference. If the source does not concretely realize the target, a plain edge or another class is the correct model.",
        "severity": "high",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "guardrail",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/guardrail.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/guardrail.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "guardrail",
        "markdown": "## Guardrail\n\nDo not use when the edge opens another graph. That is `graph.entry`, not `local.content`."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "local-content-failure-mode",
      "type": "failure-mode",
      "label": "Failure Mode",
      "position": {
        "x": 1360,
        "y": 620
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 250,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Common Failure Mode",
        "body": "The implementation relationship becomes misleading when authors draw it for loose inspiration or adjacency instead of concrete fulfillment. That makes traceability surfaces lie and weakens legend meaning.",
        "likelihood": "medium",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "failure-mode",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/failure-mode.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/failure-mode.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "failure-mode",
        "markdown": "## Failure mode\n\nIf used for outbound destinations, readers may mistake external navigation for in-graph supporting content."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "local-content-procedure",
      "type": "procedure",
      "label": "Procedure",
      "position": {
        "x": 400,
        "y": 620
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "How To Apply It",
        "body": "1. Start with a plain edge between an implementation artifact and the thing it implements.\n2. If the source concretely realizes the target, assign `graph.implements`.\n3. Leave the base edge valid and let the class provide meaning and defaults.\n4. Override styling only when the local graph needs a special emphasis.",
        "steps": [
          "Create a base edge",
          "Assign the class only when implementation is concrete",
          "Let the class own meaning",
          "Override locally only when necessary"
        ],
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "procedure",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/procedure.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/procedure.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "procedure",
        "markdown": "## Procedure\n\nAttach this class to edges like `watch` or `future` when the target content is part of the current graph experience."
      }
    },
